      "content": "It is a profound and painful realization to feel that your story has truly ended, but please know that even the darkest chapters can eventually lead to a new beginning. Sometimes, when the ink runs dry, the only honest thing to do is to close the book and rest until the sun rises again, rather than forcing yourself to write when you have nothing left to say. You are not alone in this darkness, and there are people who care about you and want to support you through it.",
